#~ msgid ""
#~ "CWA is configured so that your Calibre Database (<code>metadata.db</code> "
#~ "file) should always be somewhere in <code>/calibre-library</code>.\n"
#~ "        CWA automatically searches whatever directory you've bound to "
#~ "<code>/calibre-library</code> in your docker-compose file for existing "
#~ "Calibre\n"
#~ "        Libraries/metadata.db files on start up. If it finds just one "
#~ "exisitng library, it mounts it automatically, if it find multiple, by "
#~ "default\n"
#~ "        it will mount the largest one automatically and if it doesn't "
#~ "find any, it will automatically create and mount a new one. For more "
#~ "details,\n"
#~ "        <a href=\"https://github.com/crocodilestick/Calibre-Web-Automated/"
#~ "wiki/Configuration#database-configuration\">see here</a>!\n"
#~ "        <br><br>\n"
#~ "        Therefore, when configuring your docker-compose file for CWA, "
#~ "<b>DO NOT CHANGE THE PATHS IN THE VOLUMES SECTION ON THE RIGHT SIDE OF "
#~ "THE COLONS!</b>\n"
#~ "        These paths are internal to CWA only, you can change what they're "
#~ "bind to to your heart's content on the left-hand side but there's no "
#~ "reason to\n"
#~ "        change the paths on the right-hand side.<br><br>If you would like "
#~ "your <code>metadata.db</code> file in a different location to the rest of "
#~ "your\n"
#~ "        library, use the <b>Seperate Book Files from Library Option below "
#~ "and there, enter the path to the rest of the library</b>\n"
#~ "        <br><br>\n"
#~ "        E.g. As long as your library's <code>metadata.db</code> file is "
#~ "bound somewhere within <code>/calibre-library</code>, you could bind the "
#~ "dir\n"
#~ "        containing the corrisponding book files ect. to something like "
#~ "<code>/books</code> and enter <code>/books</code> in the field that pops "
#~ "up below\n"
#~ "        once you've checked the <b>Seperate Book Files from Library</b> "
#~ "option."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "CWA je konfiguriran tako, da mora biti vaša zbirka podatkov Calibre "
#~ "(datoteka <code>metadata.db</code>) vedno nekje v <code>/calibre-library</"
#~ "code>.\n"
#~ "CWA ob zagonu samodejno preišče kateri koli imenik, ki ste ga povezali z "
#~ "<code>/calibre-library</code> v datoteki docker-compose, za obstoječe "
#~ "datoteke Calibre Libraries/metadata.db. Če najde samo eno obstoječo "
#~ "knjižnico, jo samodejno priklopi, če jih najde več, privzeto samodejno "
#~ "priklopi največjo, če pa ne najde nobene, samodejno ustvari in priklopi "
#~ "novo. Za več podrobnosti si oglejte <a href=\"https://github.com/"
#~ "crocodilestick/Calibre-Web-Automated/wiki/Configuration#database-"
#~ "configuration\">tukaj</a>!\n"
#~ "<br><br>\n"
#~ "Zato pri konfiguriranju datoteke docker-compose za CWA <b>NE SPREMINJAJTE "
#~ "POTI V RAZDELKU VOLUMES NA DESNI STRANI DVOPIJ!</b>\n"
#~ "Te poti so notranje samo za CWA, na levi strani lahko poljubno "
#~ "spremenite, na kaj so vezane, vendar ni razloga, da bi spreminjali poti "
#~ "na desni strani.<br><br>Če želite, da je vaša datoteka <code>metadata.db</"
#~ "code> na drugi lokaciji kot preostali del vaše knjižnice, uporabite "
#~ "spodnjo možnost <b>Loči datoteke knjig od knjižnice in tam vnesite pot do "
#~ "preostale knjižnice</b>\n"
#~ "<br><br>\n"
#~ "Npr. Dokler je datoteka <code>metadata.db</code> vaše knjižnice vezana "
#~ "nekje znotraj <code>/calibre-library</code>, lahko vežete imenik, ki "
#~ "vsebuje ustrezne datoteke knjig itd. na nekaj takega kot <code>/books</"
#~ "code> in v spodnje polje vnesite <code>/books</code>, ko označite možnost "
#~ "<b>Loči knjižne datoteke iz knjižnice</b>."

